@PersistenceCapable public class A { @Unowned B b; }

@PersistenceCapable public class B {...}

Persist of an A with related B will persist the A and B (though the Key of the B will obviously have no parent Key component). Entity of A will have a property containing the Key of the related B. Loading of such objects will pull in the related object as per the Fetch Plan (which the user controls, as per the JDO spec), so when it needs the B then it does a get of the B using the Key.

